sections.text:
After section 27K of the Employment Rights Act 1996 insert—

27L Remedies

(1) Where an employment tribunal finds that a complaint under section 27K is well-founded, it may—

(a) make a declaration as to the worker's rights;

(b) order the employer to deal with qualifying tips, gratuities and service charges in a specified manner;

(c) order the employer to make a payment to the worker of such amount as the tribunal considers appropriate;

(d) order the employer to pay compensation to the worker of such amount as the tribunal considers just and equitable in all the circumstances, subject to the limit in subsection (2).

(2) The maximum amount of compensation that may be awarded under subsection (1)(d) is £5,000.
